    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated Concept",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Created By: Aly RUbino"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You started the Family Business with Ma and Pa; you drove the carriage, Ma rode shotgun, and Pa kept the jars from breaking in the back. You'd drive your dinky little carraige from Rome to Florence carrying innocent things first, medicine, bags of flour, anything the Little Guy needed. Then the cargo got bigger, riskier, as did the price and the stakes, drugs, absinthe mostly to start. When Ma retired because of her eyes, a cousin you never knew you had came on board to help run things, Gina Capone. She was a sharpshooter like you'd never seen in the dark. Pa retired not long after Gina joined and you two started hiring more cousins you'd never met, more carts, more routes. When Ma and Pa died they were buried with jewels in the coffins, which were made of simple pine. Bless their hearts they never forgot their humble beginnings. After that, things changed between you and Gina. She stopped being your cousin and became your mentor instead - teaching you how to run a proper business scheme. At first you didn't like it, but you picked up fast that Gina didn't like it when you tried to talk over her, she was a strong woman who deserved respect. One night in Summer, while you and Gina did a small run to a village next door, and wolves chased the cart. You were shotgun, and while you were as good a shot as Gina, the wolves didn't go down until she handed you silver bullets instead. That got the job done, but you had too many questions at the end of the ride, and Gina decided to bring you into the real Family Business of Lasombra, and started teaching you about where the real money was - religion. You caught on quick how to adjust to smuggling and selling goods to Cainites, it was just like selling in humans, but the price of the wrong word now was a Monomacy against an angry elder instead of a mob."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Gina Capone",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Lasombra - No Reflection"
        ],
        [
          "Embrace Date:",
          "1825.0",
          "Embrace Location:",
          "Florence, Italy",
          "",
          "Generation",
          "Pretender Elder 8"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Who You Know",
          "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        ],
        [
          "Yasmin the Black",
          "This Black Hand warlock wants to turn the old Tremere Chantry into a magical stronghold for the Sabbat"
        ],
        [
          "Kathrine \"Katie\" Ford",
          "A Black Hand infilitrator recently returned from spying on the Camarilla"
        ],
        [
          "Mourad alAbiot",
          "A Black Hand Remover from the odl days.  You scouted and bank rolled more than one mission for his people in Tierra Del Fuego"
        ],
        [
          "Chalupavka",
          "Rival for Archbishop: A monstrous Tzimsce Elder from Peru. She has strong ties to the Black Hand"
        ],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "You hear that the San Diego Chantry has fallen and there is talk of what to do with it - gut it and make it a training ground, or burn it to the ground. You don't care what happens to you, you just want in to get your hands on the goodies."
        ],
        [
          "You are a Nomadic pack, but with the fresh prospect of a new leader and new lands for the taking, who knows? San Diego is an old, Catholic city, who knows what goods can be exported. Maybe you'll stay if the pickings look good."
        ],
        [
          "Your Cousin sent you a letter last week, your biggest suppliers is asking you to set your site on San Diego, see if you can make its military presence a good breeding ground for the Black Hand."
        ],
        [],
        [
